body:
@manthey's [commit](https://github.com/python-pillow/Pillow/commit/445451c0b9347b50e0f603db33f196e207de470d) comment:

> Prior to this change, you could create a new image with a zero size. Now, you can't, but you can still crop an image to end up with an image of zero size. Is there a reason it is allowed based on some operations but not in a new image? It seems it should either be allow in both instances or neither.

@rakeshvar's commit comment:

> I strongly agree with @manthey. This check should not even be there. What is wrong with an image of size 0x0?

The commit is part of PR https://github.com/python-pillow/Pillow/pull/2146, which are fixes for https://github.com/python-pillow/Pillow/issues/2105, "Multiple memory corruption vulnerabilities".
